Install Coq and OCaml.

Download CompCert from http://compcert.inria.fr/ and unpack it here.
Rename its directory to compcert (or create a symlink).

In compcert, configure and make.

Get back to the parent directory and make.  Ignore the warnings.

Run ./test.native and you should see output 0 and 4294967295.

The filter program is to accept all IP packets.  It's taken from
the original BPF paper (Sect. 3.4), which can also be found at the
end of BPF.v.  BPF.v currently implements an (incomplete) interpreter.
